courses.title: Communities + Sponsored Row w/ Kevin Marciano, FOAD | Let's Chat

videos.name: Communities + Sponsored Row w/ Kevin Marciano, FOAD | Let's Chat
videos.path: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DgMfXfNOB5Q

segments.title: - Intro
Are there any plans to introduce targeting features to other countries?
If you have a tycoon, it doesn’t do you any good being in front of a combat/ PVP player. Will there be data targeting?
Could you target specific devices (mobile, PC cloud)?
Could it be better to change timezones? Currently uses UTC.
Are Fortnite communities intended to replace Discord?
Will you be able to support giveaways?
Will players be able to open communities in-game rather than just the link?
Will we get analytics for communities for announcements/ highlights?
Will Communities have some sort of discovery system for those that are not in the top rankings?
Will giveaway items be limited to in-game items/ V-bucks or can you promote other items (offline)?
Are there plans on expanding visibility of the row program to users under 18?
What is the reason for the 2-day lead time on submitting bids?
What about a feature to easily export the data from the campaigns?
Why does pushing an update cancel a campaign?
Will targeting include “lookalikes” (users who play X game or follow a certain creator)?
Any plans to support push notifications to mobile?
Do you plan on letting creators upload videos to their communities in the future?
Why does Sponsored Row have open slots at the end of the day that aren’t shown?
Why do some Sponsored Row stay in the auction for over 24 hours?
Why is 10 cents the minimum CPM instead of letting the market decide the minimum?
Why are there times when there are only 11 tiles?
Why do the tiles not show CCU?
Is the intention to always have dedicated real estate for Sponsored Row, or have it in other categories as well in the future?
Can you not have an A-B test running at the same time of a campaign?
Will you be able to schedule community posts in the future as well?
When viewing engagement analytics for your island have you thought about filtering people that come from Sponsored Row?
What are the top goals for Q1 next year? Something you would think would be a big win?
Is the communities feature going to receive support?
Discussion about the developer experience.
Things we’re working on.

segments.title: Intro – How are tools developed and new features implemented?
What does the product team look like as a whole, outside of your role?
How is the workload divided?
Are decisions and task prioritization usually made as a team?
What criteria determine whether a community feature request makes it to the roadmap?
How far in advance are updates ready? Was the latest update finished recently or long ago?
For ongoing, non-urgent fixes, are they worked on immediately or fit into the next update?
The roadmap was changed today and matchmaking was delayed—can you share more about that?
Will scale-based matchmaking be available in more types of games?
Can you share more about upcoming spectator improvements?
What will the Thin Client look like on release, and what can you share?
Will the Thin Client improve over time?
If a player is wearing an outfit they don’t own, can others download that skin in real time?
Can you explain the new Player Input (Experimental) device?
Will this make it easier to create more complex scenarios and options?
What is the philosophy behind the recent memory calculation changes?
Did the potential increase in mobile players factor into that decision?
Will real-time memory usage return to the editor?
Has Epic considered allowing editor-only scripted Blueprints in UEFN?
Will Fortnite characters be opened up to more scriptability (size, animations, etc.)?
Is rebuilding characters through physics from the ground up better?
Are there plans to expose static meshes, textures, etc., rather than keep them read-only?
Will UEFN get a visual scripting language similar to Blueprints?
Any plans for a Chest or Loot Pool device?
Are there plans to enable playing locally in the editor?
Are wait times something being continuously worked on?
Why were custom items and weapons delayed again? Technical or polish reasons?
Any plans to add debugging tools to Verse?
What process does Epic follow for small editor improvements and reducing friction?
What is your vision for UEFN in the coming years?

How do you balance “For You” recommendations with curated content, and have you taken any inspiration from other platform algorithms?

videos.path: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3xDzj8XyTR4

segments.title: Intro
What advice would you give to creators who want to build with respect to IP, but still create innovation and interest?
Can we use assets that aren’t in-game already, that still tie into the IP?
Is there a place where we have a hub to these IP programs? Any talk about having an IP hub for conversations, feedback, and contact with content providers?
Are there any plans to make it possible to use different characters (LEGO, Star Wars, etc.) from different IPs on the same island?
What do you think creators did really well with collabs, what did they do poorly, and what do you want to see in the future?
When releasing a new property, moderation delays can be an issue—are there future tools to achieve a “ready to launch” state?
What tools could help curate more content? (e.g. Discovery updates, item/weapon updates, universe expansions)
What are the rules for converting your Fortnite map to an IP map and vice versa?
With Paramount’s large movie library, will more IPs be brought into the ecosystem?
Will the expansion of IPs under the same umbrella be added to the same toolset?
How does your team approach translating IP to creators? How do you ensure meaningful updates?
Will there be more structured communication for launches—surprise vs. planned-out approach?
Will creators get access to a Trello-like roadmap system to preview upcoming content?
Do Epic and IP-holders prefer creators focus on fast-paced action, story-based games, or both?
Can you share any upcoming releases or surprises that creators may not be aware of yet?
